medical_history.chief_complaint: The patient was admitted to the hospital in active spontaneous labor at 39.7 weeksâ€™ gestation.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: On the day of admission, fetal movements ceased in midmorning. Spontaneous, regular contractions began approximately 4 hours later. The patient was admitted 2.5 hours after the onset of contractions.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient had a positive tuberculin skin test 4 years ago and received antituberculosis medication for 6 months. She also had a history of varicella and received the BCG vaccine as a child. There were no other relevant medical conditions specified.
medical_history.family_history: The patient's father had type 2 diabetes mellitus.
medical_history.social_history: The patient did not smoke cigarettes, drink alcohol, or use intravenous drugs. She was born and raised in West Africa and immigrated to the United States 7 years earlier. She had returned to Africa twice in the previous 3 years and had not received pretravel vaccinations or malaria prophylaxis.
